% C++ Code Ontology - CNL Format
% Natural English syntax for semantic code analysis
%
% This ontology extends the OO meta-ontology (oo_ontology.cnl) with
% C++-specific concepts. All cpp:* types are subclasses of oo:* types,
% enabling language-independent queries using the oo: prefix.

% ============================================================================
% Class Hierarchy (C++-specific)
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:Method` is a `cpp:Function`.
Every `cpp:Constructor` is a `cpp:Method`.
Every `cpp:Destructor` is a `cpp:Method`.
Every `cpp:Operator` is a `cpp:Method`.

% ============================================================================
% Meta-Ontology Integration (extends oo_ontology.cnl)
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:TranslationUnit` is a `oo:Module`.
Every `cpp:Namespace` is a `oo:Namespace`.
Every `cpp:Class` is a `oo:Class`.
Every `cpp:Struct` is a `oo:Class`.
Every `cpp:Function` is a `oo:Function`.
Every `cpp:Method` is a `oo:Method`.
Every `cpp:Constructor` is a `oo:Constructor`.
Every `cpp:Destructor` is a `oo:Destructor`.
Every `cpp:Operator` is a `oo:Method`.
Every `cpp:Field` is a `oo:Field`.
Every `cpp:Parameter` is a `oo:Parameter`.
Every `cpp:UsingDirective` is a `oo:Import`.
Every `cpp:UsingDeclaration` is a `oo:Import`.

% ============================================================================
% Enum Types
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:Enum` is a `oo:Enum`.
Every `cpp:EnumClass` is a `oo:Enum`.
Every `cpp:Enumerator` is a `oo:EnumValue`.

% ============================================================================
% Exception Handling (Try/Catch/Throw)
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:TryBlock` is a `oo:TryBlock`.
Every `cpp:CatchClause` is a `oo:CatchClause`.
Every `cpp:ThrowStatement` is a `oo:ThrowStatement`.

% ============================================================================
% Control Flow Statements
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:ReturnStatement` is a `oo:ReturnStatement`.
Every `cpp:BreakStatement` is a `oo:Statement`.
Every `cpp:ContinueStatement` is a `oo:Statement`.
Every `cpp:GotoStatement` is a `oo:Statement`.

% Note: Call tracking uses "calls" role relationships instead of cpp:Call instances
% This enables uniform call graph analysis across all languages

% ============================================================================
% Literals (for magic number detection)
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:IntegerLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.
Every `cpp:FloatingLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.
Every `cpp:StringLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.
Every `cpp:CharacterLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.
Every `cpp:BooleanLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.
Every `cpp:NullptrLiteral` is a `oo:Literal`.

% ============================================================================
% C++ Built-in Types
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:int` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:long` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:short` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:char` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:bool` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:float` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:double` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:void` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:auto` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:unsigned` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:signed` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:size_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:ptrdiff_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:nullptr_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:wchar_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:char8_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:char16_t` is a `cpp:Type`.
Every `cpp:char32_t` is a `cpp:Type`.

% ============================================================================
% Template Support
% ============================================================================

Every `cpp:TemplateClass` is a `cpp:Class`.
Every `cpp:TemplateFunction` is a `cpp:Function`.
Every `cpp:TemplateParameter` is a `cpp:Parameter`.
